stickerText: Here‚Äôs what 2050 could look like if we half emissions every decade
You walk outside the air is moist and fresh
Air is cleaner than it has been since before the industrial revolution
Cooperate donations and public money funded biggest tree plant in human history
Every vacant block, or alley is converted into a shady grove
Roof tops are floral or a vegetable garden.
Concrete empty building are now covered in vines and flora. 75% of population in cities
High speed rail replaces domestic flights
We no longer burn fossil fuels
There are some countries that can afford nuclear use it. Most energy comes from, wind, solar, geothermal, and hydro. Which is Basically free.
Houses produce their own electricity, Every surface is covered with solar paint, that harvest solar
Excess electricity has made desalination possible. Everyone in the world will have access to fresh drinking water.
Agriculture evolved more tree based, Forest cover worldwide is at 50%
Timberland with grazing, regenerative agriculture, perennial crops, sustainable grazing, approved crop rotation
Most food comes from local farmers and producers. Animal meat, and dairy products have practically disappeared from diets, processed foods has also diminished.
Health has increased, price decrease a reduction in cancers, heart attacks and strokes has been seen
More people in cities use public transport, bikes, walk
Biofuels replace jet-fuel with international flights, the cost of flights are higher, people spend more time at their destination
The gases that are already there, are still causing extreme weather, but less extreme than the alternative
glaciers and artic ice are still melting, sea still rising, severe droughts and desertification is still occurring western USA, metteraian, and parts of China
Countries understand that it‚Äôs in everyone‚Äôs interest to work together
We have return to being apart of nature. Which future do you choose?
